    "# Networks\n",
    "\n",
    "Networks are the basic building blocks of deeppy, defined as:\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "def __init__(self, arch_params, task = \"reg\", criterion = nn.MSELoss, device = None,\n",
    "\t\t\t\t\t   optimizer = optim.AdamW, lr = 0.01, weight_decay = 0 , scheduler_params = None):\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Every network at least consists of: \n",
    "\n",
    "1) model     -> nn.Sequential neural network | (arch_params)\n",
    "2) optimizer -> torch.optim optimizer        | (optimizer, lr, weight_decay)\n",
    "3) scheduler -> deeppy.utils.Scheduler       | (scheduler_params)\n",
    "\n",
    "And these methods:\n",
    "\n",
    "1) optimize(X) - given a dataset X and defined criterion, perform one step optimization\n",
    "2) forward(X)  - given a dataset X, computer f(x)\n",
    "3) autoencode(X), decode(X) - for autoencoder architectures encode-decode"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3b58448a-3166-41f3-9793-90a016332e9c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## deeppy.networks.network.LayerGenerator\n",
    "\n",
    "An architecture is defined by arch_params parameter, that uses a LayerGenerator.\n",
    "A LayerGenerator generates repetative layers given layer size. For example with the following parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "layer_generator_params = {\n",
    "    \"layers\" : [obs,64,32,16],\n",
    "    \"type\" : nn.Conv2d,\n",
    "    \"decs\" : [nn.MaxPool2d],\n",
    "    \"args\" : [{\"kernel_size\" : 4} , {\"kernel_size\" : 2}],\n",
    "    \"hidden_act\" : nn.ReLU,\n",
    "    \"out_act\" : nn.Sigmoid,\n",
    "    \"weight_init\" : \"uniform\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "We will get a CNN network with 3 layers, where every layer has a Conv2d with kernel size 4 followed by MaxPool2d kernel size 2 and a ReLU layer. The output layer of this network is sigmoid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 52,
   "id": "b75b0a7e-874f-451b-9fef-43a66125b3bd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Network(\n",
      "  (criterion): MSELoss()\n",
      "  (model): Sequential(\n",
      "    (0): Conv2d(3, 64, kernel_size=(4, 4), stride=(1, 1))\n",
      "    (1): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)\n",
      "    (2): ReLU()\n",
      "    (3): Conv2d(64, 32, kernel_size=(4, 4), stride=(1, 1))\n",
      "    (4): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)\n",
      "    (5): ReLU()\n",
      "    (6): Conv2d(32, 16, kernel_size=(4, 4), stride=(1, 1))\n",
      "    (7): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)\n",
      "    (8): Sigmoid()\n",
      "  )\n",
      ")\n",
      "----------\n",
      "inp shape : torch.Size([2, 3, 160, 210])\n",
      "out shpae : torch.Size([2, 16, 17, 23])\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
